{
  "stem": "18654.4",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 246.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And they didn't want to know, because she married out.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "They wouldn't help me in any way whatsoever.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "They wouldn't even find anything out.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "Because we wanted to have her buried properly.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "I was very hard up at the time.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "I couldn't go there, because I didn't have the money.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And eventually the people were-- who really helped me were the St.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "John's Ambulance Brigade.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "Because I'd read in one report-- because I used to get papers and letters and things-- that she was an officer in the St.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "John's Ambulance Brigade.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And I approached the St John's Ambulance Brigade in London.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And they took the trouble to see me, the head of the brigade saw me in London, and interviewed me, and they helped me an awful lot, and so did the head of the police in Trinidad, who was an Englishman, and came home on leave and he took the trouble to come and see me, although he lived in Cornwall.",
      "word_count": 61
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And I asked him to try and find a few things of hers which were from Germany still.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "They'd all disappeared.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "There was nothing, nothing.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "He had destroyed or sold or got rid of everything.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And eventually, when they did-- it was a very unpleasant case, the way the whole-- the-- the murder was a very unpleasant murder.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And it took the headlines for weeks and weeks.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "It did appear in the British press once or twice.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "And eventually my cousin, my older cousin that I've mentioned before, we put a gravestone up, which of course is still there and is being looked after.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "And he was hanged for it.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
